x = 21.36 / 0.12
x = 178

To solve for x, we divide both sides of the equation by 0.8: x = 16,000 / 0.8 = 20,000. The value of the vehicle last year was 20,000 dollars.

0.04x ≥ 310
x ≥ 310 / 0.04
x ≥ 7750

So Trenton must make at least 7750 dollars in sales to reach his goal.
